 Clooney gift bag

 Los Angeles, March 17 (AFP): Actor-director George Clooney, who won the best supporting actor Oscar this year for Syriana, has donated his luxury items-laden Oscars gift bag for auction to benefit US hurricane victims, a leading charity said.

 The bags, handed out to participants in the Annual Academy Awards ceremony, held this year on March 5, are loaded with thousands of dollars worth of gifts. 

 Kilo hotel

 Berlin (Reuters): A hotel in northern Germany has started charging its guests by the kilo for an overnight stay. In the town of Norden, guests now have to step onto the scales before moving into their rooms and fork out half a euro per kilogram. Heckrodt, the hotel owner, said he hoped his initiative would inspire Germans to become healthier. 




